{{Italic title}} {{Taxobox | name = Lentisphaerae aranesa | domain = [[Bacteria]] | phylum = [[Lentisphaerae]] |classis = [[Lentisphaeria]] <small>Cho et al. 2012</small> |ordo = [[Lentisphaerales]] <small>Cho et al. 2004</small> | familia = [[Lentisphaeraceae]] <small>Cho and Hedlund 2012</small> | genus =''[[Lentisphaera]]'' <small>Cho et al. 2004</small> | species ='''''L. araneosa''''' | binomial = '''''Lentisphera araneosa''''' | binomial_authority = Cho et al. 2004<ref>{{cite journal|last1=Parte|first1=A.C.|title=Lentisphaera|journal=www.bacterio.net|url=http://www.bacterio.net/lentisphaera.html}}</ref> | type_strain = | subdivision = | synonyms = }}
'''''Lentisphera araneosa''''' is a [[Marine biology|marine]] [[bacteria]] strain in the bacterial [[phylum]] [[Lentisphaerae]]. They are able to produce [[viscous]] [[transparency and translucency|transparent]] [[expolymer]]s and grow attached to each other by the [[polymer]] in a [[three-dimensional]] configuration. They are part of the natural surface bacterial population in the Atlantic and Pacific oceans. They are less than 1% of the total bacterial community. This species is [[gram negative]], [[non-motile]], [[non-pigmented]], [[Aerobic organism|aerobic]], [[chemoheterotropic]], and facultatively [[oligotrophic]] sphere-shaped.<ref>{{Cite journal| last1 = Cho | first1 = J. C.| last2 = Vergin | first2 = K. L.| last3 = Morris | first3 = R. M.| last4 = Giovannoni | first4 = S. J.| title = Lentisphaera araneosa gen. Nov., sp. Nov, a transparent exopolymer producing marine bacterium, and the description of a novel bacterial phylum, Lentisphaerae| journal = Environmental Microbiology| volume = 6| issue = 6| pages = 611–621| year = 2004| pmid = 15142250| doi = 10.1111/j.1462-2920.2004.00614.x}}</ref><ref>{{cite journal|last1=Choi|first1=Ahyoung|last2=Yang|first2=Seung-Jo|last3=Rhee|first3=Kwang-Hyun|last4=Cho|first4=Jang-Cheon|title=Lentisphaera marina sp. nov., and emended description of the genus Lentisphaera|journal=International Journal of Systematic and Evolutionary Microbiology|date=April 2013|volume=63|issue=4|doi=10.1099/ijs.0.046433-0|pages=1540–1544|pmid=22888188}}</ref> Its [[genome]] has been sequenced.<ref>{{cite journal|last1=Thrash|first1=J. Cameron|last2=Cho|first2=Jang-Cheon|last3=Vergin|first3=Kevin L.|last4=Morris|first4=Robert M.|last5=Giovannoni|first5=Stephen J.|title=Genome Sequence of Lentispheara araneosa HTCC2155T, the Type Species of the Order Lentisphaerales in the Phylum Lentisphaerae|journal=Journal of Bacteriology|date=June 2010|volume=192|issue=11|pages=2938–2939|doi=10.1128/JB.00208-10|pmid=20363947|pmc=2876483}}</ref>
